    <text>
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01109.001.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten">
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</salute>
                        <salute>Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p><persName>Benjamin O. Sheckells</persName> of <placeName>Washington D.C.</placeName> having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned, and having refused or failed to file in your Office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the Act of Congress entitled, "An Act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>" Approved <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>.</p>
                    <p>You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">12th July 1862</date>. The undersigned resided in <placeName>Washington</placeName> before and at the time of the passage of said act of <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date> with her owners consent&#8212;</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Description</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row rend="handwritten">
                            <cell><persName>Anna Pinyer</persName></cell>
                            <cell>Female</cell>
                            <cell>50 years</cell>
                            <cell>light Mulatto</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Ann Pinyer</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                            <signed><persName>Jno. M. Hanson</persName></signed>                        
                    </closer>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01109.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>paid</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Ann Pinyer</persName> Schedule</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 65</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-07-25">25th July 1862</date>.</ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>The Commissioners satisfied on the testimony of <persName>Eliza Ann <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">Drane</unclear></persName> of the truth of within statement order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></ab>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                clerk</signed>
                        <dateline><date when="1862-07-26">July 26, 1862</date></dateline></closer>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><choice><abbr>Cert.</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> given. <choice><abbr>Idfd</abbr><expan>Identified</expan></choice> by <gap reason="illegible" extent="about three words" unit="chars" quantity="14"/></ab>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
            </div1>                      
        </body>
